            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p><span><span><span><span><span><span>The few housing programs for returning citizens provide communal living spaces. Often these programs operate on a rigid and controlling system. Returning Citizens have been incarcerated and forced to be housed with people based upon the fact that they have been found guilty of a crime. However, when they return home, it is important that they are able to shed the stigma of incarceration and reentry. Having a home of oneâ€™s own is paramount to healing from incarceration and prior trauma as well as successful reentry.

                <br><br>HFA pilot program will begin in the fall of 2022 in Washington, D.C. Four returning citizens will be given individual apartments. WSFM will cover the cost of the rental units for one year as well as provide wrap around services that include huma development. Years one to five will see the purchase of 4 buildings across DC with six to eight units. The housing will be free for those who are unable to pay rent and low cost to others. The housing is permanent. This program is designed to be scaled nationally.
